
[1]dismount

   DISMOUNT, v.i. [dis and mount.]

   1. To alight from a horse; to descend or get off, as a rider from a
   beast; as, the officer ordered his troops to dismount.

   2. To descend from an elevation.

                               DISMOUNT, v.t.

   1. To throw or remove from a horse; to unhorse; as, the soldier
   dismounted his adversary.

   2. To throw or bring down from any elevation.

   3. To throw or remove cannon or other artillery from their carriages;
   or to break the carriages or wheels, and render guns useless.
